<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/267a</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Yokohama</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Scidmore</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-05"><hi rend="italic">January 5,
                                        1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Following for <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> [from
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WD1">Willard</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>Your cable 4th.<note n="1" xml:id="d328fn1">Not printed; see telegram
                                    from the Ambassador in Japan, Jan. 2, 4 p.m., <ref target="frus1918Russiav02#pg_17">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 17</ref>.</note> Fifty thousand dollars
                                cabled January 3 for <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName>.
                                Have answered all your cables. Advise immediately if matter is now
                                fixed. Do not be discouraged. You will not be deserted. Am hoping
                                you will still find opportunity to do great good.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>